{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-219-modern-user-interaction-on-ios"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-219-Modern-User-Interaction-on-iOS"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/219\/","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"abstract":[{"text":"Touch user interactions are fundamental to the user experience on iOS. Learn how to master the power of UIKit’s gesture recognizer system in your application. Find out how to integrate with the new Drag and Drop features and the system gestures. Get some great tips for debugging your custom built interactions.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-221-Introducing-PencilKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-804-Designing-Across-Platforms"],"type":"links","style":"list"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Modern User Interaction on iOS"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-221-Introducing-PencilKit":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-221-introducing-pencilkit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Meet PencilKit, Apple’s feature-rich drawing and annotation framework. With just a few lines of code, you can add a full drawing experience to your app — with access to a canvas, responsive inks, rich tool palette and drawing model. Hear the technical details that make a great Apple Pencil experience. Learn about the new screenshot editor and how you can adopt just a few small APIs to enable your full content to be captured beyond the size of the screen, with or without your app’s user interface."}],"role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-221-Introducing-PencilKit","title":"Introducing PencilKit","kind":"article"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-804-Designing-Across-Platforms":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-804-Designing-Across-Platforms","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-804-designing-across-platforms","abstract":[{"text":"Learn techniques for determining which Apple platforms are right for your app and how to create a great user experience by designing for the unique capabilities and strengths of each platform.","type":"text"}],"title":"Designing Across Platforms","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"url":"\/documentation\/w